==English==

===Pronunciation===
*(''[[RP]]''): /ˈɡɑːdən/, /<tt>"gA:d@n</tt>/
*(''US''): gärʹdən, /ˈɡɑːrdən/, /<tt>"gA:rd@n</tt>/

===Etymology===
Old Northern French ''[[gardin]]'', a variant of Old French ''[[jardin]]'', a diminutive of ''[[jart]]'', borrowed from Old Franconian ''*gard'', from Germanic ''*garda-'' (Old English ''[[geard|ȝeard]]'').

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# A decorative place outside, usually where plants are grown for food (''vegetable garden'') or ornamental purposes (''flower garden'').
#(''in plural'' '''gardens''') Such an ornamental place to which the public have access.
# The grounds at the front or back of a house.
#(''as a [[modifier]]'') Of, relating to, in, from or for use in a garden
#:''garden salad'' (= a salad from a garden)
#:''garden shed'' (= a shed in a garden)
#{{rfv-sense}} {{slang}} The [[pubic hair]].

